OL,6,FEighteen of these failed. Sixteen of
OL,7,Fthese were for allowing cadets under
OL,8,Fthe age of 18 to illegally purchase
OL,9,Fknives and bladed articles. The other
OL,10,Ftwo were for failing the Challenge 25
OL,11,Fpolicy, where sellers challenge anyone
OL,12,Fthey think is under 25 for proof of
OL,13,Fage.
OL,15,FCounty Superintendent Doug Downing
OL,16,Fsaid, "The stores were given oral
OL,17,Fwarnings or words of advice. We all
OL,18,Fhave a role to play in ensuring knife
OL,19,Fcrime is addressed in our communities."
